#How to delpoy our application in the cloud AWS


1- Create an acount AWS 
2- Get Id's from : https://console.aws.amazon.com/iam/home?region=eu-west-3#/security_credentials (clé d'accés)
3- installation of AWS cli
4- Do the access to the file ~/.aws/credentials
enter to the file main.tf we add : 

provider "aws" {
  shared_credentials_file = "~/.aws/credentials"
  region = "eu-west-3"  # Europe (Paris)
}

5- Create a bucket https://s3.console.aws.amazon.com/s3/home?region=eu-west-3
6- enter the name of the bucket in main.tf
7- création of dynamoDB https://eu-west-3.console.aws.amazon.com/dynamodb/home
clé = LockID
tom de la table : poca-tfstates-locks
8- changement of @ ip elastic in integration.tfvar 
https://eu-west-3.console.aws.amazon.com/ec2/v2/home?region=eu-west-3#Addresses:
9- get ssm id https://console.aws.amazon.com/billing/home?#/account
replace 182500928202 by your id all places in terraform's reporetry
10- after the terraform init command replace the xxx in the command : export TF_VAR_db_password="xxx" par mot de passe de 8 caractères de votre choix
11- after the deployment has been validated to access your application you must recover the ipv4 address of the ec2 instance https://eu-west-3.console.aws.amazon.com/ec2/v2/home?region=eu-west-3#Instances:instanceState=running


 
